Proactive supply-chain defense for the modern Python ecosystem.

Spectr is a high-speed security gatekeeper that performs multi-layered forensic
analysis of PyPI packages and metadata to detect typosquatting, skeleton
packages, reputation anomalies, and other supply-chain threats before they
reach your environment.

---

## Quick Start

### Instant Audit (no install)

Analyze a package quickly using `uvx` (if available):

```bash
uvx spectr check <package_name>
```

### Install for Permanent Protection

Install Spectr and enable shell hooks so `pip` and `uv` invocations are
automatically audited:

```bash
pip install spectr
spectr --install-hook
```

After installation, common package operations will be intercepted and
evaluated by Spectr before any network download or local install proceeds.

## Usage & Administration

Common commands:

```text
spectr --install-hook     # Inject security aliases into ~/.bashrc / ~/.zshrc
spectr --disable          # Emergency bypass: remove shell interceptions
spectr --sign <package>   # Authorize a package and update the integrity hash
spectr --json             # Output analysis results in JSON
spectr --verbose          # Show detailed forensic metrics
```

## Integrity & Whitelisting

Spectr maintains a cryptographically signed whitelist at `~/.spectr-whitelist`.

- To trust a package: `spectr --sign <package_name>`
- Spectr verifies the SHA256 signature of the whitelist automatically before
  every scan.

Unauthorized manual modifications to the whitelist will be detected and will
trigger a security alert.

## Security Heuristics

Spectr applies a defense-in-depth model that includes:

- **Typosquatting detection** ‚Äî identifies look-alike package names (e.g.
  `reqests` vs `requests`).
- **Structural analysis** ‚Äî flags tiny or skeletal sdists (often < 2 KiB).
- **Identity verification** ‚Äî highlights suspicious maintainer metadata and
  brand-jacking patterns.
- **Behavioral velocity** ‚Äî monitors automated/repeated release patterns that
  may indicate abuse or bot activity.

## Feature Comparison

| Feature          |                             pip / uv |                         Spectr (v0.21.1+) |
| ---------------- | -----------------------------------: | ----------------------------------------: |
| Primary goal     | Installation & dependency resolution |          Supply-chain defense & forensics |
| Trust model      |               Implicit (trusts PyPI) |       Zero-trust (heuristic verification) |
| Deep scan        |                                   No | Recursive auditor (scans dependency tree) |
| Security posture |        Reactive (post-install scans) |         Proactive (pre-download analysis) |
| Output           |                        Progress bars |        ve auditor (scans dependency tree) |
| Security posture |        Reactive (post-install scans) |         Proactive (pre-download analysis) |
| Output           |                        Progress bars |                   Forensic reports & JSON |

